{
  "stem": "1033.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They had a paper called I guess it means 'the paper that watches after the people,' if I try to translate it.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "My German wasn't ever that great.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "But I did learn a bit of German.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And I studied German in school prior to the camps.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] One incident stands out in mind.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "It was in Kaufering, in Lager 3, where a person was stealing potatoes.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And there were big signs that anybody gets caught will be killed.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Anyhow, he was captured.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And he was put between the electrified wire and the little single wire that ran on the inside.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And he had to stand there, with a potato in his mouth, for like two, three, days.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "We could all see him.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "He wasn't killed.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And as I told you before, this commandant put me in the kitchen.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "So he saved my life.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And he was still the commandant.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And after the war, I found out that this commandant was hung by the inmates in the camp.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "So it's, it's, it's, it's really a, a, a very difficult thing for me to, to stand in judgment.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Apparently, this person with the potato in his mouth survived, then hung him after the war for having been punished.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "It's, it's-- you know, there are a lot of gray areas that are-- I think, for heroism and greatness, a human must have an opportunity.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And then he must feel equal to it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And some take that opportunity.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And many don't.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "Many don't even know that there is an opportunity.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "I was still not old enough to really, really know what I know today.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] But it's an incident that stands out in my mind.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "The other thing is singing and bringing back the dead.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "It seemed bizarre to me-- going to work singing.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And, and generally, the younger SS guards were much more brutal than the older people.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "By then I did, but not on the train, not, not, not even while they were telling us which way to go.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had no idea.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And nobody did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We thought we were going to take-- be taken to a place where there'd be work for everyone, and we'll be better treated.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that's that.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And that was the pleasant thing that we all wanted to believe, in spite of the horrible stories that people whispered about-- of people being shot, people being asked to dig their graves, and then they were shut into it.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] It was not unknown.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But I certainly never believed it, not until when I saw that amazing movie.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And, and, and, and like, like a cold wave coming over me, it was precisely like that, when you see those people coming in with their suitcases and giving their names proudly-- Rosenberg, Wasserman-- and walking away with their paper stamped.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And when you see the-- two months later-- the suitcases being empty, thrown out of the window, and these people are like nothing-- like flotsam and jetsam, like nothings.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And, and, and, and the world goes on.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the little voice inside every one of us-- certainly inside me, and all of us-- keeps asking questions, keeps wondering why, keeps wondering how could we make it better?",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "How could something like this gone on and how-- excuse me-- how a thing like this must never, ever go on.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Going back again, you said that you were quite sick.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "What happened to you?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, as we got to-- I didn't know it was Dachau.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We got in this place at night.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we heard some-- by, by then, we all knew-- like, through seven layers of fog-- we knew that the war was coming to an end.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And there was some commotion in the morning.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I ran to the-- to the-- to the fence.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And by then, the fence was not electrified and put the-- I-- you know, and I grabbed the fence.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I saw soldiers coming in.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There were about three or four corpses on the-- on the right side of us as we were standing in a group.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "They were German soldiers.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I saw a man with something on his back coming closer and closer to me.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I was there, waving.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I didn't know what the thing on his back was.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And, you know, I never talked to my children about this, not until recently, because I didn't want to weaken them.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And you know, it couldn't possibly contribute to their-- I was going to say 'predicament,' but I'll change that to 'opportunities.' And, and, and when I looked at the picture, [LAUGHS] I couldn't believe my eyes.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There I am, waving!",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I wrote to the writers.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
